<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,150,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Murakami, Y." box="[324,524,150,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="249 - 253" refId="ref48888" refString="Murakami, Y. (1980) Current topics on the chestnut gall wasp - experience in China. Agriculture and Horticulture, 55, 249 - 253. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1980">Murakami (1980)</bibRefCitation>
provided references for each distribution record, but they were not listed in the references section.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,150,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,222,248]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kamiya, K." box="[362,533,222,249]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="49 - 50" refId="ref45428" refString="Kamiya, K. (1959) Gall insects injurious to trees. Forest Pests News, 8, 49 - 50." type="journal article" year="1959">Kamiya (1959)</bibRefCitation>
addressed several cynipid species. However, he did not mention the distribution of any of them, except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu" authorityYear="1951" box="[457,606,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuriphilus">
<emphasis box="[457,606,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">D. kuriphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[622,692,258,284]" name="Japan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Japan</collectingCountry>
). Hence, we have not included this reference in any other species throughout this catalogue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,150,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,357,330,356]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks (3).</emphasis>
This species is a harmful pest for 
<taxonomicName box="[754,860,331,357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,860,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Castanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees and many papers addressing its control have been published to date. Some of these publications indirectly mention the range of this species (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Murakami, Y. &amp; Umeya, K. &amp; Oho, N." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="197 - 203" refId="ref49014" refString="Murakami, Y., Umeya, K. &amp; Oho, N. (1977) A preliminary introduction and release of a parasitoid (Chalcidoidea, Torymidae) of the chestnut gall wasp, Dryocosmus kuriphilus Yasumatsu (Cynipidae) from China. Japanese Journal of Applied Entomology and Zoology, 21 (4), 197 - 203. [in Japanese] https: // doi. org / 10.1303 / jjaez. 21.197" type="journal article" year="1977">
Murakami 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. 1977
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kato, K. &amp; Hijii, N." box="[258,465,402,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref45478" refString="Kato, K. &amp; Hijii, N. (1993) Optimal clutch size of the chestnut gall-wasp, Dryocosmus kuriphilus Yasumatsu (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Population Ecology, 35 (1), 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02515640" type="journal article" year="1993">Kato &amp; Hijii 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moriya, S. &amp; Shiga, M. &amp; Adachi, I." box="[477,688,402,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="407 - 415" refId="ref48623" refString="Moriya, S., Shiga, M. &amp; Adachi, I. (2003) Classical biological control of the chestnut gall wasp in Japan. In: Van Driesche, R. G. (Ed.), Proceedings of the 1 st International Symposium on Biological Control of Arthropods. United States Department of Agriculture, Forest Service, Morgantown, West Virginia, pp. 407 - 415." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Moriya 
<emphasis box="[566,616,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhu, D. - H. &amp; He, Y. - Y. &amp; Fan, Y. - S. &amp; Ma, M. - Y. &amp; Peng, D. - L." box="[700,874,402,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="279 - 284" refId="ref56066" refString="Zhu, D. - H., He, Y. - Y., Fan, Y. - S., Ma, M. - Y. &amp; Peng, D. - L. (2007) Negative evidence of parthenogenesis induction by Wolbachia in a gallwasp species, Dryocosmus kuriphilus. Entomologia Experimentalis et Applicata, 124 (3), 279 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1570 - 7458.2007.00578. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Zhu 
<emphasis box="[752,802,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Matsuo, K. &amp; Yara, K. &amp; Kagoshima, K. &amp; Tuda, M. &amp; Moriya, S." box="[886,1100,402,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="100 - 102" refId="ref47131" refString="Matsuo, K., Yara, K., Kagoshima, K., Tuda, M. &amp; Moriya, S. (2011) Finding of Torymus koreanus (Hymenoptera: Torymidae) attacking Dryocosmus kuriphilus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in Japan. Entomological Science, 14 (1), 100 - 102. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1479 - 8298.2010.00416. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Matsuo 
<emphasis box="[977,1026,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,150,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,438,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasumatsu" authorityYear="1951" box="[303,565,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuriphilus">
<emphasis box="[303,565,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Dryocosmus kuriphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a purely parthenogenetic species, by loss of the sexual generation from an ancestral cyclically parthenogenetic lifecycle (
<bibRefCitation author="Murakami, Y." box="[672,858,474,500]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="249 - 253" refId="ref48888" refString="Murakami, Y. (1980) Current topics on the chestnut gall wasp - experience in China. Agriculture and Horticulture, 55, 249 - 253. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1980">Murakami 1980</bibRefCitation>
). It induces large integral galls in the buds, petioles and leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[306,500,510,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis box="[306,412,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Castanea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(Table 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
